By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) – The presidential candidate of the All Progressives Congress (APC), Bola Tinubu and his running mate, Kashim Shettima on Wednesday promised to provide good governance if elected at the February 25, 2023 election. The APC flag bearer made the promise at the Sani Abacha Stadium in Kano where he vowed not to disappoint Nigerians. The APC presidential candidate who addressed a crowd of supporters also promised to keep his campaign promises. The vice presidential candidate, who spoke in Hausa, also promised that the APC administration will complete the gas pipeline project and other important projects in Kano. The Governor of Kano State, Abdullahi Ganduje, in his address, said Kano is the biggest state for democracy in Nigeria. Sundiata Post recalls that other party members who were present at the rally including the National Chairman of the party, Abdullahi Adamu; governors among others. They and other party faithful expressed optimism about their victory in the 2023 elections. Senator Kashim Shettima, Asiwaju Bola Tinubu’s running mate says he’s never seen a political gathering like Kano APC Presidential Campaign rally.